<br>
After playing a while with them I have noticed that the haste can be a hinderance. The haste is very good, but only lasts 15 seconds. What is bad about it is that it overwrites the Theurg haste buff. Yup you lose a 10 minute buff for a 15 sec proc. So I changed my set up.<br>
<br>
DoT is great and I was thinking of going for 2 of them. If one dot sticks and 2 seconds later another dot fires, it will overwrite the 1st one. I never saw that as a bad thing because at least you will refresh it and keep your target in pain.<br>
<br>
But I finally went for the dot/dd combo. DoTs are so popular that every fellow meleer out there is going to have it on his weapon(s). In that case mass overwriting can become a waste. So I got an energy DD for the off hand jambya. Does about 100 now and then. My RvR sabre also has a dot, so I can still do dot/dot in 1 vs 1 RvR.<br>
<br>
